Suspected gunmen on Saturday evening reportedly shot four people to dead at a mining site in Dong Village, Jos North Local Government Area of Plateau State. Sources revealed that no fewer than four men were shot dead and a woman who survived a gunshot is receiving treatment in the hospital. A community leader Emmanuel Dong confirmed the attack. According to him, the attack occurred around at 6:00 p.m. The spokesman of the Plateau State Police Command, Gabriel Ubah an Assistant Superintendent of Police (ASP) confirmed the attack to The Nation on phone yesterday. - Advertisement - Ubah, said: “We are aware of the attack and four people were killed.   Police probe death of man in Ebonyi     Court orders takeover of building over public safety     Fire razes markets in Delta, Anambra, Abia   The Command has deployed armed police men to the area and calm has returned to the area. The member representing Jos South/Jos East in the National Assembly, Dachung Musa Bagos described the killing as “one death, too many.” He empathised with the families of Lo-Bwong of Lo-Tang, in Hwolshe, Jos South Local Government Area over the inhumane and cold blooded killing of members of their family by callous and bloodthirsty bandits. In a statement by his media adviser, Danja Dafwam Yaks, said, the recent massacre which resulted in the death of three of his constituents, one other person; and a woman recuperating in the hospital occurred at Dong Village. The member said the incident has raised concerns over the readiness of security agencies to tackle once and for all the gorilla style of killing which has been the case for more than two decades. He frowned at the easy means where small arms and light weapons find their ways indiscriminately into the country and moved around the country without traces. He called on the Federal and state governments to urge the security agencies to take more seriously the insecurity around the state and the country at large.